Model.Game

Class PutMoveValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • Model.Game.PutMoveValidator

  • public class PutMoveValidator
extends java.lang.Object
    This class has several methods that are used to validate whether a PutMove is valid on a provided Board. Created by Martijn on 30-1-2016.

      • validMove

        public boolean validMove()
                  throws InvalidMoveException
        This method is called by other classes to check this move's validity on the board. If the move is invalid in any way, an InvalidMoveException is thrown.
        Returns:
        True if the move is valid on the board.
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveException - When the move is invalid in any way.

      • validPut

        private boolean validPut()
                  throws InvalidMoveException
        Checks whether a PutMove is valid. A PutMove is invalid if all Tiles in a line have the same color and a different shape or all the same shape and different shape. The same Tile in a line is not allowed and the move must be connected to the field, but may not override it.
        Returns:
        True if the move is valid on this board.
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveException - If the move is invalid.

      • validPositioning

        private boolean validPositioning()
                          throws InvalidMoveException
        Checks whether a move is either all on one horizontal line or all on one vertical line and within Configuration.RANGE distance from one another. Also checks whether the move set has duplicates.
        Returns:
        True if the Location of the move is valid
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveException

      • validIdentity

        private boolean validIdentity()

        Throws:

      • orthogonalLine

        private java.util.List<Tile> orthogonalLine(Axis axis,
                                  Location location,
                                  Location startPoint,
                                  int step)
        Creates a List of Tiles from the field that form a line with the Tile that lies on startPoint. This method is recursive.
        Parameters:
        axis - Axis on which the line lies.
        location - Location of Tile that is checked.
        startPoint - Location of the original Tile from the move that is checked.
        step - Step the X or Y takes (1 or -1).
        Returns:
        A List of Tiles that form a line with the Tile that lies on startPoint.

      • validLine

        private boolean validLine(Axis axis,
                Location location,
                int step)
                   throws InvalidMoveException
        Checks whether a move with a certain axis is valid on the field. This method only checks the horizontal or vertical line, depending on the axis given. It's a recursive method that uses a given location and increases either the X or Y variable (again, depending on the given axis) by the given step. The step variable is either 1 or -1.
        Parameters:
        axis - Axis on which the line lies.
        location - Location of Tile that is checked.
        step - Step the X or Y takes (1 or -1).
        Returns:
        True if the move does not violate any game rules on the line.
        Throws:
        InvalidMoveException
